  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      RATIONALE: Studying samples of tumor tissue from patients with cancer in the laboratory may
      help doctors learn more about changes that occur in DNA and identify biomarkers related to
      cancer. It may also help doctors understand how patients respond to treatment.

      PURPOSE: This laboratory study is looking at gene expression in patients with advanced or
      metastatic colorectal cancer receiving bevacizumab.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      OBJECTIVES:

        -  Determine whether the balance of splice form expression alters susceptibility of tumors
           in vivo to respond to anti-VEGF therapy.

      OUTLINE: Tumor tissue samples collected on clinical trial E-3200 are analyzed for laboratory
      endpoints.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
